[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now a man named Ananias, together with Sapphira his wife, sold a piece of property. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " kept back for himself part of the proceeds with his wife’s knowledge; he brought"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " only part of it and placed it at the apostles’ feet. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Peter said, “Ananias, why has Satan filled"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit and keep back for yourself part of the proceeds from the sale of"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the land? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Before it was sold,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did it not"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " belong to you? And when it was sold, was the money"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " not at your disposal? How have you thought up this deed in your heart?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You have not lied to people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but to God!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Ananias heard these words he collapsed and died, and great fear gripped"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " all who heard about it. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the young men came,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " wrapped him up,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " carried him out, and buried"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After an interval of about three hours,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his wife came in, but she did not know"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what had happened. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter said to her, “Tell me, were the two of you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " paid this amount"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for the land?” Sapphira"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “Yes, that much.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter then told her, “Why have you agreed together to test the Spirit of the Lord? Look! The feet of those who have buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " At once"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " she collapsed at his feet and died. So when the young men came in, they found her dead, and they carried her out and buried her beside her husband. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Great"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " fear gripped"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the whole church"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and all who heard about these things."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now many miraculous signs"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and wonders came about among the people through the hands of the apostles. By"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " common consent"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they were all meeting together in Solomon’s Portico."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " None of the rest dared to join them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but the people held them in high honor."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " More and more believers in the Lord were added to their number,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " crowds of both men and women. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Thus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they even carried the sick out into the streets, and put them on cots and pallets, so that when Peter came by at least his shadow would fall on some of them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " A crowd of people from the towns around Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " also came together, bringing the sick and those troubled by unclean spirits."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were all"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " being healed."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now the high priest rose up, and all those with him (that is, the religious party of the Sadducees"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "),"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and they were filled with jealousy."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " laid hands on"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the apostles and put them in a public jail. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But during the night an angel of the Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " opened"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the doors of the prison,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " led them out,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Go and stand in the temple courts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and proclaim"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the people all the words of this life.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they heard this, they entered the temple courts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at daybreak and began teaching."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Now when the high priest and those who were with him arrived, they summoned the Sanhedrin"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – that is, the whole high council"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the Israelites"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – and sent to the jail to have the apostles"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " brought before them."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But the officers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who came for them"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did not find them in the prison, so they returned and reported,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We found the jail locked securely and the guards standing at the doors, but when we opened them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " we found no one inside.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now when the commander"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the temple guard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the chief priests heard this report,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they were greatly puzzled concerning it,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " wondering what this could"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " be. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But someone came and reported to them, “Look! The men you put in prison are standing in the temple courts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and teaching"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the people!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the commander"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the temple guard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went with the officers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and brought the apostles"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " without the use of force"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (for they were afraid of being stoned by the people)."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they had brought them, they stood them before the council,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the high priest questioned"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saying, “We gave"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you strict orders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " not to teach in this name."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Look,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you have filled Jerusalem"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with your teaching, and you intend to bring this man’s blood"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on us!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Peter and the apostles replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We must obey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God rather than people."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The God of our forefathers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " raised up Jesus, whom you seized and killed by hanging him on a tree."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God exalted him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to his right hand as Leader"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Savior, to give repentance to Israel and forgiveness of sins."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And we are witnesses of these events,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and so is the Holy Spirit whom God has given to those who obey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now when they heard this, they became furious"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and wanted to execute them."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But a Pharisee"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " whose name was Gamaliel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a teacher of the law who was respected by all the people, stood up"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the council"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and ordered the men to be put outside for a short time. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then he said to the council,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Men of Israel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " pay close attention to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what you are about to do to these men. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For some time ago"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Theudas rose up, claiming to be somebody, and about four hundred men joined him. He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was killed, and all who followed him were dispersed and nothing came of it."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After him Judas the Galilean arose in the days of the census,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and incited people to follow him in revolt."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He too was killed, and all who followed him were scattered. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So in this case I say to you, stay away from these men and leave them alone, because if this plan or this undertaking originates with people,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it will come to nothing,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but if"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it is from God, you will not be able to stop them, or you may even be found"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " fighting against God.” He convinced them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and they summoned the apostles and had them beaten."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " they ordered them not to speak in the name of Jesus and released them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So they left the council rejoicing because they had been considered worthy"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to suffer dishonor for the sake of the name."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And every day both in the temple courts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and from house to house, they did not stop teaching and proclaiming the good news"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that Jesus was the Christ."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]